    {
        "content": "<p>I wanted to prove something like the following.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">variable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℕ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Fin</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∀</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Fin</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"o\">),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">j</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∈</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">unitInterval</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∏</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∈</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">unitInterval</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">apply</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">prod_mem</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- tactic 'apply' failed, failed to unify</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- @Membership.mem ?M ?B SetLike.instMembership (∏ c ∈ ?t, ?f c) ?S</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- with</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- @Membership.mem ℝ (Set ℝ) Set.instMembership (∏ n : Fin n, f n) unitInterval</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>but <code>prod_mem</code> takes <code>{S : B} [SubmonoidClass B M]</code>, while <code>unitInterval</code> is just a <code>Set ℝ</code>. Which is the best way to do this?</p>",
        "id": 450302287,
        "sender_full_name": "Yoh Tanimoto",
        "timestamp": 1720564454
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This works:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">unitIntervalSubmonoid</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Submonoid</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">carrier</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">unitInterval</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">one_mem'</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">unitInterval</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">one_mem</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">mul_mem'</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">unitInterval</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">mul_mem</span>\n\n<span class=\"kd\">@[</span><span class=\"n\">simp</span><span class=\"kd\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">coe_unitIntervalSubmonoid</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">unitIntervalSubmonoid</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">unitInterval</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rfl</span>\n<span class=\"kd\">@[</span><span class=\"n\">simp</span><span class=\"kd\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">mem_unitIntervalSubmonoid</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∈</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">unitIntervalSubmonoid</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↔</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∈</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">unitInterval</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Iff</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rfl</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∏</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∈</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">unitInterval</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">refine</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">prod_mem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">S</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">unitIntervalSubmonoid</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">?_</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">simpa</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">using</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 450307242,
